A Fort Myers man has completed the Ironman Triathlon in Kona, Hawaii. 
Jason Gunter, an attorney, completed the 2.4-mile swim, 112-mile bike ride, and the 26.2-mile marathon in 16 hours. 
More than 2,300 athletes competed in this year's event. 
Gunter is a former Cape Coral firefighter who lost part of his right arm and left leg in a 1992 boating accident.
